Wife of the President Aisha Buhari has felicitated with Nigerians especially Christian faithful as they celebrate this year’s Easter. Easter is the commemoration of the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ in Christendom. The First Lady took to her Twitter handle send her congratulatory message on Friday in Abuja. She wrote,” As we celebrate Good Friday and Easter, I am extending my best wishes to Nigerians especially our Christian brothers and sisters. ”It is significant to commemorate Christ’s death and resurrection as a reminder of His virtues of harmony and peaceful coexistence among humanity. ”Let us also remember to keep praying for God’s protection and an end to the COVID-19 pandemic.”